Built in 2022, this Lennar home features over 2,700 square feet with an additional 1 bedroom-1 bath unit perfect for extended family living. This two-story home has a very spacious open floor plan with extra-large living and dining areas with easy access to the chef’s kitchen. The kitchen is complete with brushed gray stainless-steel appliances, a large kitchen island, granite counter-tops and high-end cabinets. The master suite has a large walk-in shower a dual vanity, tile flooring huge walk-in closet and a ceiling fan. Two additional great size secondary bedrooms all with good closet space. You also have a wonder flex space or what Lennar is calling the “Next-Gen Living.” It is a separate living area with its own bedroom, bathroom, and small kitchen. Perfect for the extended family of for members of the family staying a bit long that expected. A very private oversize and I mean oversized rear yard with patio and fresh landscaping makes for a great second living area. The refrigerator is included along with a 3-car garage with opener, tankless hot water system and solar are just a few of the man many extras the home provides. Hurry this home will not last for long.

Please see the map attached for the best directions

Rent includes Lawn care

Visit www.select1realty.com for additional information specific to this property. You may apply online right from this page; just click the Apply Now button.

Screening Guidelines:
1. All individuals planning on living at the property, over the age of 18, must apply. Application fee is $52.00 per adult.
2. A credit score of at least 700 is required for this property.
3. Good rental references. No evictions, no exceptions.
4. A household monthly income of at least 3.5 times the monthly rent amount (or a verifiable cash reserves).
5. If self-employed, documents for year-to-date income and past two years IRS 1040 are required.
6. No pets unless otherwise stated on the property page of our web site. If acceptable, an additional pet deposit is required for each pet.
7. Tenancy must start within 2 weeks from the approval of your application.
8. This is a non-smoking home and renter's insurance is required.


For REDUCED move in costs, talk to us about our Security Deposit Replacement Program!

Resident Benefit Package(RBP):
All residents are enrolled in the Resident Benefits Package (RBP) which includes HVAC air filter delivery, our best-in-class resident rewards program, identity protection, and much more! More details upon application.

Call Select 1 Realty at (925) 706-9000 for additional information or to schedule an appointment to view this property. Application requirements can be found at www.select1ealty.com; simply click on Tenant Services and Application

The construction of this one-bedroom studio has recently been completed and you will be the first tenant to make it your home! You will have your own driveway parking for one car and a separate entrance, including a patio. When you walk in through the front you will fall in love with the vinyl hardwood floor that is gorgeous and easy to clean. The kitchen has a clean quartz countertop and includes a refrigerator, dishwasher, microwave, and convection hot plate. Please keep in mind that the hot plate only works with stainless steel pots and pans. The bathroom is beautifully constructed and has a quartz countertop sink and a large walk-in shower with a modern sliding glass door. Right next to that is the new stacked washer and dryer unit. The bedroom is well-sized and has a ceiling fan to help you circulate the cold air from the AC unit. Staying cool will be easy because every room has a ductless AC unit with their own remotes. The mailing address is only assigned to the main house, so you will need to set up a PO box for personal mail and a different shipping location to receive packages. Utilities to include internet, electric, water, trash, and gas will be a monthly flat rate to the tenant for $150.

At Pure Property Management of Alabama, we offer two options for security deposits. The first option is a traditional security deposit, where a lump sum is paid at move-in and is held on account for the duration of your tenancy.  The security deposit can be used to pay for any unpaid charges, including rent and utilities, damages, and/or cleaning needed at move-out.   If your account does not have a final balance due, then the full security deposit amount will be refunded. The second option is our Security Deposit Replacement Program. With this option, you will pay a monthly non-refundable fee for the duration of your tenancy instead of the traditional upfront deposit. No funds will be held to use towards any balance on your account at the time of move out. You as the tenant will still be responsible for any charges assessed at move-out.

Sorry, no pets.

Introducing the brand new smoke-free apartment community located in the historic West End of Santa Rosa - a luxurious oasis designed to cater to your every need. Nestled in an upbeat and serene neighborhood, this apartment community offers a perfect blend of urban sophistication and tranquility.

The community boasts an enclosed courtyard with a sparkling pool, surrounded by lush greenery, where you can take a dip and unwind after a long day. Adjacent to the pool, you will find a BBQ area with a fire pit, perfect for hosting weekend get-togethers with family and friends.

As you enter the modern and active lobby, you can relax and socialize with other residents. Adjacent to the lobby is a lounge area you will be greeted by a coffee bar where you can savor a cup of coffee while catching up on your emails.

The community offers a package storage area with an Amazon locker, ensuring that you never miss a delivery. If you are a fitness enthusiast, the fitness center is well-equipped with state-of-the-art equipment, allowing you to maintain your fitness routine with ease.

The community also offers community offices/workspaces, where you can work in a professional environment without having to leave the comfort of your apartment community. A conference room is also available for meetings or other professional engagements.

For pet lovers, the community offers a dog wash station and a dog run, allowing your furry friend to enjoy the outdoors. Additionally, the community also provides a bike storage/repair area, allowing you to conveniently store and maintain your bicycle.

"For REDUCED move in costs, talk to us about our Security Deposit Replacement Program!" We offer two options for security deposits. The first option is a traditional security deposit, where a lump sum is paid at move-in and is held on account for the duration of your tenancy.  The security deposit can be used to pay for any unpaid charges, including rent and utilities, damages and/or cleaning needed at move-out.   If your account does not have a final balance due, then the full security deposit amount will be refunded. The second option is our Security Deposit Replacement Program. With this option, you will pay a monthly non-refundable fee for the duration of your tenancy instead of the traditional upfront deposit. No funds will be held to use towards any balance on your account at time of move out. You as the tenant will still be responsible for any charges assessed at move out. If your account does not have a final balance due, then the full security deposit amount will be refunded. The second option is our Security Deposit Replacement Program. With this option, you will pay a monthly non-refundable fee for the duration of your tenancy instead of the traditional upfront deposit. No funds will be held to use towards any balance on your account at time of move out. You as the tenant will still be responsible for any charges assessed at move out. You can apply today by visiting us at https://huntsville.ahiproperties.com/huntsville-homes-for-rent.

At Pure Property Management of Alabama, we offer two options for security deposits. The first option is a traditional security deposit, where a lump sum is paid at move-in and is held on account for the duration of your tenancy.  The security deposit can be used to pay for any unpaid charges, including rent and utilities, damages, and/or cleaning needed at move-out.   If your account does not have a final balance due, then the full security deposit amount will be refunded. The second option is our Security Deposit Replacement Program. With this option, you will pay a monthly non-refundable fee for the duration of your tenancy instead of the traditional upfront deposit. No funds will be held to use towards any balance on your account at the time of move out. You as the tenant will still be responsible for any charges assessed at move-out.

At Pure Property Management of Alabama, we offer two options for security deposits. The first option is a traditional security deposit, where a lump sum is paid at move-in and is held on account for the duration of your tenancy.  The security deposit can be used to pay for any unpaid charges, including rent and utilities, damages, and/or cleaning needed at move-out.   If your account does not have a final balance due, then the full security deposit amount will be refunded. The second option is our Security Deposit Replacement Program. With this option, you will pay a monthly non-refundable fee for the duration of your tenancy instead of the traditional upfront deposit. No funds will be held to use towards any balance on your account at the time of move out. You as the tenant will still be responsible for any charges assessed at move-out.

Pets are considered on a case-by-case basis with homeowner approval. A Pet Administration Fee is charged for each Pet; $400 for the 1st pet and $250 for each additional pet. Tanked, caged or animals kept in an enclosure will be charged $250 per enclosure. (Examples include fish in tanks, birds in cages, and lizards kept in an enclosure.) Each applicant is required to complete the appropriate pet profile. This also includes those applicants with no pets. Applicants with pet(s) accept the non-refundable fee of $25. This registration is free for those applicants with no pets or those with certified assistance animals. To qualify for an American Avenue rental property, the combined household income must be 3x the monthly rent. For Section 8 renters, we require the combined household income be 3x the residents rent responsible portion of the monthly rent.

Average combined resident score must meet minimum requirements. Guarantors (including local Housing Authorities & Voucher Programs) are accepted and must meet outlined guarantor requirements.

Additional terms and requirements apply. All applications are processed in the order in which they are completed and received. Application does not guarantee a lease.

American Avenue is an Equal Housing Lessor under the FHA. Applicable local, state and federal laws may apply. Lease terms and conditions apply. This is not an offer to rent—you must submit additional information for review and approval. Listing features may not be accurate and should be confirmed with an American Avenue leasing representative.

Avoid rental scams! American Avenue does not list homes for lease through Craigslist, Social Serve, or any other classified advertising services.
